INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '2a64f326-9dda-4473-812b-80ca6062158c',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$OpenAPI — Designing REST Resources, Verbs, and Status Codes That Actually Mean Something$escape$,
  $escape$OpenAPI's `paths` object is where REST intent becomes contract. Resource naming should reflect nouns, never verbs — `/users/{userId}/orders` not `/getOrdersForUser`. Each path operation maps to a single HTTP verb, and OpenAPI enforces this by letting you define `get`, `post`, `put`, `patch`, and `delete` as sibling keys under a path item.

Idempotency matters for tooling: OpenAPI marks `get`, `put`, and `delete` as idempotent by convention, which retry-aware HTTP clients respect. Document this explicitly by setting `x-idempotent: true` on `post` endpoints that support idempotency keys (e.g. Stripe-style payment creation).

Status codes in OpenAPI's `responses` map are not suggestions — code generators and mock servers use them to produce typed response models. Distinguish `200 OK` (resource returned) from `201 Created` (with a `Location` header pointing to the new resource) and `204 No Content` (successful delete). Avoid catch-all `200` responses; each code should reference a distinct `$ref` schema so clients get accurate types per outcome.$escape$,
  $escape$paths:
  /users/{userId}/orders:
    get:
      operationId: listUserOrders
      responses:
        '200':
          description: Paginated orders
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/OrderPage'
    post:
      operationId: createOrder
      x-idempotent: true
      parameters:
        - in: header
          name: Idempotency-Key
          schema:
            type: string
          required: true
      responses:
        '201':
          description: Order created
          headers:
            Location:
              schema:
                type: string
        '409':
          description: Duplicate idempotency key
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Error'$escape$,
  $escape$bash$escape$,
