INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '00b32dc8-0eba-46ea-8e9e-1fd917036fbb',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$OpenAPI Rate Limiting — Documenting Per-Endpoint, Per-User Policies with Sliding Window vs Token Bucket$escape$,
  $escape$OpenAPI doesn't enforce rate limits, but it's the contract layer where you document them precisely. Start by defining reusable response headers in `components/headers`: `X-RateLimit-Limit`, `X-RateLimit-Remaining`, `X-RateLimit-Reset` (epoch seconds for sliding window) or `X-RateLimit-Reset-After` (seconds until refill for token bucket). Attach these to every `200` and `429` response object on rate-limited paths.

For per-endpoint policies, use `x-ratelimit` vendor extensions directly on the `PathItem` or `Operation` object — most API gateways (Kong, AWS API Gateway, Azure APIM) consume these to generate enforcement rules. For per-user scoping, pair `x-ratelimit-scope: user` with a `securityScheme` reference so the gateway keys the counter to the authenticated identity from the JWT `sub` claim.

Sliding window semantics map to `X-RateLimit-Reset` (absolute timestamp), while token bucket maps to `Retry-After` (relative delay). Document both `429` headers explicitly — clients need to distinguish them to implement correct backoff. Never omit the `Retry-After` header from your `429` response schema; it's part of RFC 6585 and most SDKs auto-handle it.$escape$,
  $escape$components:
  headers:
    X-RateLimit-Limit:
      schema: { type: integer }
    X-RateLimit-Remaining:
      schema: { type: integer }
    Retry-After:
      schema: { type: integer }

paths:
  /v1/completions:
    x-ratelimit:
      scope: user
      strategy: token-bucket
      requests: 60
      window: 60s
    post:
      responses:
        '200':
          headers:
            X-RateLimit-Limit:
              $ref: '#/components/headers/X-RateLimit-Limit'
            X-RateLimit-Remaining:
              $ref: '#/components/headers/X-RateLimit-Remaining'
        '429':
          headers:
            Retry-After:
              $ref: '#/components/headers/Retry-After'
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/RateLimitError'$escape$,
  $escape$bash$escape$,
