INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '5d7ecde8-8a68-42d0-b824-9b906b255bd0',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$OpenAPI + Problem+JSON — Defining Consistent Error Schemas Across Every Endpoint$escape$,
  $escape$RFC 9457 (Problem Details) gives your API a machine-readable error contract. In OpenAPI 3.1, define a reusable `ProblemDetails` schema in `components/schemas` with the canonical fields: `type` (URI), `title`, `status`, `detail`, and `instance`. Reference it from every `4xx`/`5xx` response using `$ref: '#/components/schemas/ProblemDetails'` and set `content` to `application/problem+json` — not `application/json`. This forces generated clients to deserialize errors correctly and signals to consumers that all errors share one shape.

Extend for domain errors by composing `allOf`: your `ValidationProblem` adds an `errors` map on top of the base schema. Document this in `components/responses` as a named response (`BadRequest`, `NotFound`) and reuse those refs across operations — a single source of truth. When you regenerate SDKs with tools like `openapi-generator` or `kiota`, all error types map to typed exceptions automatically, eliminating ad-hoc string parsing of error payloads across REST, webhooks, and server-sent event error frames.$escape$,
  $escape$components:
  schemas:
    ProblemDetails:
      type: object
      properties:
        type:     { type: string, format: uri }
        title:    { type: string }
        status:   { type: integer }
        detail:   { type: string }
        instance: { type: string, format: uri }
    ValidationProblem:
      allOf:
        - $ref: '#/components/schemas/ProblemDetails'
        - type: object
          properties:
            errors:
              type: object
              additionalProperties:
                type: array
                items: { type: string }
  responses:
    BadRequest:
      description: Validation failed
      content:
        application/problem+json:
          schema: { $ref: '#/components/schemas/ValidationProblem' }
paths:
  /users:
    post:
      responses:
        '400': { $ref: '#/components/responses/BadRequest' }$escape$,
  $escape$bash$escape$,
